TITLE: Setting Up Lexical Editor with Plugins
DESCRIPTION: Basic setup of a Lexical editor with initial configuration and essential plugins. The LexicalComposer is the root component that provides context to all plugins.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/react/plugins.md#2025-04-13_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
const initialConfig = {
  namespace: 'MyEditor',
  theme,
  onError,
};

<LexicalComposer initialConfig={initialConfig}>
  <PlainTextPlugin
    contentEditable={<ContentEditable />}
    placeholder={<div>Enter some text...</div>}
  />
  <HistoryPlugin />
  <OnChangePlugin onChange={onChange} />
  ...
</LexicalComposer>;
```

