TITLE: Transform with Precondition to Prevent Infinite Loops
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to implement a transform with a proper precondition check. This prevents the transform from running multiple times unnecessarily by checking the current state before applying changes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/concepts/transforms.md#2025-04-13_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// When a TextNode changes (marked as dirty) make it bold
editor.registerNodeTransform(TextNode, textNode => {
  // Important: Check current format state
  if (!textNode.hasFormat('bold')) {
    textNode.toggleFormat('bold');
  }
}
```

