TITLE: Initializing and Persisting Lexical Editor State
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to initialize a Lexical editor with state loaded from a backend and then persist changes. Demonstrates the basic pattern of loading and saving editor state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/facebook/lexical/blob/main/packages/lexical-website/docs/concepts/editor-state.md#2025-04-13_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
// Get editor initial state (e.g. loaded from backend)
const loadContent = async () => {
  // 'empty' editor
  const value = '{"root":{"children":[{"children":[],"direction":null,"format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1}],"direction":null,"format":"","indent":0,"type":"root","version":1}}';

  return value;
}

const initialEditorState = await loadContent();
const editor = createEditor(...);
registerRichText(editor, initialEditorState);

...

// Handler to store content (e.g. when user submits a form)
